          Jun 22, 2017                         - RelSci Data Update                

          Institutional Holdings Changes      




Background Information:


Scoggin Management LP »
Scoggin Management directly or indirectly invests on behalf of their clients in securities of companies in which they believe that one or more potential catalysts may materially affect the value of those securities. These catalysts generally involve significant corporate events (such as mergers, acquisitions, divestitures, spin-offs, and reorganizations), financial distress or other special situations. Scoggin also invests in securities of distressed companies, bank debt, high yield bonds and other special situation securities.




In The News:




